entry.title: STAT KIT® 750-AI Emergency Medical Kit
entry.summary:
Vendor: AOSS Medical Supply
Type: Emergency Stat Kit
Price: 1895.00

The STAT KIT® 750-AI is an advanced emergency medical kit that includes non-IV and IV emergency drugs and resuscitation devices designed for office practices, radiology and outpatient imaging centers, and office-based surgical facilities. With a secure, durable mobile hard case, the 750 is designed to help medical professionals provide a range of support from basic life support (BLS) to advanced cardiac life support (ACLS). The STAT KIT® 750-AI model includes both adult and pediatric epinephrine auto-injectors.

Emergency Medication Management Program
HealthFirst Emergency Medication Management Service (EMM) offers a full suite of pre-formulated STAT KIT® emergency medical kits, devices and training to ensure you are ready for a medical emergency. All medications in STAT KITs are automatically replenished prior to expiration and are tracked in the OnTraq online compliance portal. OnTraq inventories your kit contents, tracks your emergency medications and equipment and automatically replenishes them before they expire. At any time, you can see the status of your medications and manage your account through OnTraq.

Ships directly from the manufacturer. Additional shipping charges may apply.

*Requires Physician's License to Purchase. All orders will be held until License is Received.*

entry.title: Blood Pressure Monitor Kit SunTech Tango M2 for Q-Stress & Accessories
entry.summary:
Vendor: Mortara Instrument, Inc.
Type: Blood Pressure Monitor
Price: 10523.60

SunTech Tango M2 BP Monitor Kit for Q-Stress version 6.x - additional mount kit may be required.

The Tango M2 is a reliable, automated blood pressure monitor which provides dual blood pressure measurement modes for cardiac stress and exercise testing.

Features:

  • Seamless Integration: The Tango offers automated communication with your stress system and reduces the risk of transcription errors.
  • Non-Exercise BP Mode: This monitor allows blood pressure measurements during patient set-up and recovery without an ECG signal.
  • Stat Mode: The rapidly repeated automatic BP measurements are ideal for time sensitive and emergent situations.
  • Color LCD: The Tango M2 features an improved 7" color LCD display.
  • Verify Measurements: You can see and hear the Korotkoff sounds using the onscreen display and included headphones.
  • Data Retrieval: This model offers easy troubleshooting with the 300 BP reading history and USB capabilities for measurement retrieval.
  • Field Upgrades: The USB port allows for field upgrades, ensuring end-users the most up-to-date software
  • E-Library: The Tango M2 includes an onboard E-Library with step-by-step interface notes and tutorials.
  • Interfaces: The Tango M2 model integrates with all popular stress ECG systems which use RS-232, BNC, ECG cable only for internal ECG & USB connections.
